<p><em>Stevo</em>: The notorious producer to-be started out as a DJ with a taste for the avant-garde, and thereby a remarkably non-DJ attitude towards pleasing the crowd:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Raised in Suffolk, but often mistaken for a working-class east London boy, Stevo was a fan of all kinds of weird music. Dismissing punk as â€˜just rock â€˜nâ€™ roll played badly â€¦ not that revolutionaryâ€™, he looked to more avant-garde or electronic outfits â€“ TG, Cabaret Voltaire, The Residents, Chrome, Metaboliste. He started out as a DJ, playing exactly this kind of non-crowd-pleasing material. â€˜I was more interested in terrorizing the dance floor. I used to go out just to fuck the audienceâ€™s heads,â€™ he says. (p.477)</p>
